</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5697FFFB1885C47D82DE6E6160D7F" blockId="18.[151,1437,222,319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="315">
This species group unites all 
<emphasis id="B92EB56DFFB1885C46922DE7E4B00CB6" box="[477,497,223,246]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="315">O</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName id="4C5A12FCFFB1885C45472DE6E7C20CB7" box="[520,643,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplosmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EB56DFFB1885C45472DE6E7C20CB7" box="[520,643,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="315">Hoplosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species, which i) have the metanotum not overhung by the scutellum, ii) are characterized by an apically flattened and uniformly punctured clypeus, iii) nest in preexisting cavities other than snail shells and iv) use leaf pulp as nest building material.
</paragraph>
